{"type":"message","id":"2fb97878","parentId":"403b0a76","timestamp":"2026-05-08T08:05:40.563Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b50edda3b38b0c26bd90c040bbbe]\nou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68: 先解决一个数据源的问题， Sorftime mcp 30000次，你测试过了没有图片。只有关键词之类的支持 tiktokshop 1688 亚马逊。\n2，如果是 ECHOTIK 数据平台，api我是你买不起，只能是网页会员，需要浏览器操作。同理1688 也可以浏览器操作。 是否可以行。成功率多高。"}],"timestamp":1778227540432}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b50edda3b38b0c26bd90c040bbbe\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-05-08 16:05 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"8054b1b2","parentId":"2fb97878","timestamp":"2026-05-08T08:05:40.565Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"687ac95c","parentId":"8054b1b2","timestamp":"2026-05-08T08:06:05.731Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about data source options:\n\n1. **Sorftime MCP** - 30,000 API calls, needs testing\n   - Only supports keyword-based search\n   - Data sources: TikTok Shop, 1688, Amazon\n\n2. **EchoTik** - No API access, only web membership with browser operations\n\n3. **1688** - also browser operations\n\nThe question is: Can OpenClaw interact with these browser-based platforms? And what's the success rate?\n\nLet me think about what OpenClaw can do:\n\n1. **MCP (Model Context Protocol)** - OpenClaw supports MCP servers. Sorftime has an MCP with 30,000 calls. I should check if this MCP is available and how to use it.\n\n2. **Browser automation** - OpenClaw has canvas functionality which can capture screenshots of web pages. There's also the ability to do web scraping via web_fetch.\n\nFor browser-based operations:\n- `canvas` tool can take screenshots of URLs\n- `web_fetch` can extract content from URLs\n- But these are read-only operations\n\nFor actual browser automation (filling forms, clicking, etc.), OpenClaw doesn't have a built-in browser automation tool. However, I could potentially use:\n- `exec` to run command-line tools like Playwright or Puppeteer\n- Or use the canvas to interact with web pages\n\nLet me think about the practical options:\n\n**Sorftime MCP:**\n- If Sorftime provides an MCP server, I can connect to it via `mcporter` skill\n- This would give structured API access\n- 30,000 calls should be enough for a decent workflow\n\n**EchoTik / 1688 browser-based:**\n- These would require browser automation\n- Options:\n  1. Use `exec` + Playwright/Puppeteer script\n  2. Use canvas to take screenshots and then analyze with AI\n  3. Use web_fetch to get page content\n\nThe canvas snapshot feature can capture rendered web pages and let me interact with them, while web_fetch extracts readable content from URLs. For actual browser automation like form filling or clicking, I'd likely need to use exec with a headless browser script. The most practical approach would be to first test Sorftime's MCP connection, then evaluate whether browser-based data extraction through canvas or web_fetch can handle EchoTik and 1688.\n\nSince Sorftime MCP provides 30,000 free calls, that's probably the better starting point before relying on browser automation. I should check if OpenClaw can connect to this MCP server through the mcporter skill.","thinkingSignature":"919eab5f34f508b874957f9c01aa57dbc38d5f9737ac31603590e6b3463cf15b"},{"type":"text","text":"好问题！让我测试一下 Sorftime MCP 是否能用，同时评估浏览器操作的可行性。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ib33yrf5i4gc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/mcporter/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":135,"output":587,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":48854,"totalTokens":49576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778227540565,"responseId":"064ccc55a0cc58da329f7d7f600d78c6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc436620","parentId":"687ac95c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T08:06:05.792Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ib33yrf5i4gc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: mcporter\ndescription: List, configure, authenticate, call, and inspect MCP servers/tools with mcporter over HTTP or stdio.\nhomepage: http://mcporter.dev\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"📦\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"mcporter\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"mcporter\",\n              \"bins\": [\"mcporter\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install mcporter (node)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# mcporter\n\nUse `mcporter` to work with MCP servers directly.\n\nQuick start\n\n- `mcporter list`\n- `mcporter list <server> --schema`\n- `mcporter call <server.tool> key=value`\n\nCall tools\n\n- Selector: `mcporter call linear.list_issues team=ENG limit:5`\n- Function syntax: `mcporter call \"linear.create_issue(title: \\\"Bug\\\")\"`\n- Full URL: `mcporter call https://api.example.com/mcp.fetch url:https://example.com`\n- Stdio: `mcporter call --stdio \"bun run ./server.ts\" scrape url=https://example.com`\n- JSON payload: `mcporter call <server.tool> --args '{\"limit\":5}'`\n\nAuth + config\n\n- OAuth: `mcporter auth <server | url> [--reset]`\n- Config: `mcporter config list|get|add|remove|import|login|logout`\n\nDaemon\n\n- `mcporter daemon start|status|stop|restart`\n\nCodegen\n\n- CLI: `mcporter generate-cli --server <name>` or `--command <url>`\n- Inspect: `mcporter inspect-cli <path> [--json]`\n- TS: `mcporter emit-ts <server> --mode client|types`\n\nNotes\n\n- Config default: `./config/mcporter.json` (override with `--config`).\n- Prefer `--output json` for machine-readable results.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778227565792}}
